I"<p>Changing the resolution of your screen can greatly change the way things look on your screen. Text too small? Change your screen resolution.</p>

<p>Changing the size of your desktop is done by changing the resolution of your screen. Here are the steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Right Click on your desktop (anywhere except on an icon).
    <ul>
      <li>Select [click on] Properties. The <em>Display Properties</em> dialog box will open.
        <ul>
          <li>Click on the Settings Tab.
            <ul>
              <li>Find the <em>Screen Area</em> Slider.
                <ul>
                  <li>To make your screen area smaller, drag the slider toward <em>less</em>. To make your screen area larger, drag your slider toward <em>more</em>. [Generally, 800 X 600 or 1024 X 768 are the best settings.]
                    <ul>
                      <li>Once you have adjusted the screen to the desired size, click <em>Apply</em>.
                        <ul>
                          <li>You will get a message saying that Windows will now re size your desktop. Click <em>OK</em>.
                            <ul>
                              <li>Your computer will now re size your screen and then ask you if you want to keep the new setting.
                                <ul>
                                  <li>Click <em>Yes</em> or No and then click OK to close the display properties dialog box.&lt;/p&gt;</li>
                                </ul>
                              </li>
                            </ul>
                          </li>
                        </ul>
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

